we're going to get some answers.

69
00:03:34.320 --> 00:03:36.280
Is he guilty. or is he not guilty?

70
00:03:36.880 --> 00:03:40.600
[ominous music playing]

71
00:03:42.360 --> 00:03:44.960
Hm. Umâ€¦

72
00:03:45.040 --> 00:03:50.680
{\an8}I met Michael Jackson in. uh. 1970.

73
00:03:50.760 --> 00:03:53.120
He was 12. I was 14.

74
00:03:53.920 --> 00:03:56.440
- And we became friends.
- [pensive music playing]

75
00:03:56.520 --> 00:03:59.400
- I told you that I love Michael.
- Uh-huh.

76
00:03:59.480 --> 00:04:00.480
You love Michael.

77
00:04:00.560 --> 00:04:04.280
[Randy] As a musician. you can see
the genius of Michael Jackson.

78
00:04:04.360 --> 00:04:06.320
[man 1] On stage since the age of fiveâ€¦

79
00:04:06.400 --> 00:04:08.000
[woman] Michael Jackson is a superstar.

80
00:04:08.080 --> 00:04:11.000
[Reagan] â€¦for the outstanding example
you have set for the youth of Americaâ€¦

81
00:04:11.080 --> 00:04:13.320
[man 2] The album is still number one
after 57 weeks.

82
00:04:13.400 --> 00:04:17.120
[Randy] <i>Thriller </i>is still. to this day.
the biggest-selling record of all time.

83
00:04:17.960 --> 00:04:21.200
[man 3] His album <i>Thriller.</i>
the winner of seven Grammy Awards.

84
00:04:21.280 --> 00:04:26.120
