122
00:06:26.600 --> 00:06:28.680
{\an8}His hair's kind of messy.

123
00:06:28.760 --> 00:06:31.080
{\an8}He looks as though
he hadn't slept for very long.

124
00:06:31.160 --> 00:06:33.160
[speaking indistinctly]

125
00:06:35.480 --> 00:06:41.720
And it had been some years
since he was the King of Pop.

126
00:06:42.600 --> 00:06:44.920
And yet. there's nobody comparable

127
00:06:45.000 --> 00:06:47.960
to the size and magnitude
of a Michael Jackson.

128
00:06:48.040 --> 00:06:51.440
And the other thing that obviously caused
an enormous amount of interest

129
00:06:51.520 --> 00:06:53.400
were the scandals that surrounded him

130
00:06:53.480 --> 00:06:57.120
and allegations of child sexual abuse
some years previously.

131
00:06:57.640 --> 00:07:02.000
I said. "I'd love to make a film with you
if you were interested."

132
00:07:02.080 --> 00:07:04.880
He said.
"Okay. come and see me in California."

133
00:07:05.680 --> 00:07:07.240
[Randy] Talking about it with Michael.

134
00:07:07.320 --> 00:07:10.680
I came to understand the reason
Michael was interested in Martin Bashir

135
00:07:10.760 --> 00:07:13.840
was because of his interview
with Princess Diana.

136
00:07:13.920 --> 00:07:16.280
who was somebody
Michael really kind of idolized.

137
00:07:16.360 --> 00:07:18.720
[speaking indistinctly]

138
00:07:18.800 --> 00:07:21.440
[Randy] He wanted to be portrayed
in a more human way

139
00:07:21.520 --> 00:07:24.840
{\an8}by the guy who did it for Princess Diana.

140
00:07:25.880 --> 00:07:28.200
{\an8}But Michael didn't do enough research

141
00:07:28.280 --> 00:07:30.320
because if he had. he would have realized

142
00:07:30.400 --> 00:07:34.600
that the Martin Bashir/Princess Diana
interview was kind of a disaster.

143
00:07:34.680 --> 00:07:37.440
{\an8}[Martin] Do you think
Mrs. Parker Bowles was a factor

144
00:07:37.520 --> 00:07:39.720
{\an8}in the breakdown of your marriage?

145
00:07:39.800 --> 00:07:42.200
{\an8}Well. there were three of us
in this marriage.

146
00:07:42.280 --> 00:07:44.560
{\an8}so it was a bit crowded. [laughs sadly]

147
00:07:44.640 --> 00:07:48.720
{\an8}That was the interview in which
she talked about three in a marriage.

148
00:07:48.800 --> 00:07:52.000
and it really set her at odds
with the Royal Family.

149
00:07:52.080 --> 00:07:57.440
and itâ€¦ itâ€¦
it was a public relations disaster.

150
00:07:57.520 --> 00:08:00.280
But Michael didn't follow the story
all the way to that.

151
00:08:00.360 --> 00:08:03.200
He just stopped at the point
where he wanted to do it

152
00:08:03.280 --> 00:08:04.680
because Princess Diana did it.

153
00:08:05.520 --> 00:08:08.320
Michael trusted Martin Bashir.
and then Martin Bashir.

154
00:08:08.400 --> 00:08:10.840
he was looking for a great story.

155
00:08:10.920 --> 00:08:15.920
And Michael sort of handed him
this opportunity on a silver platter.

156
00:08:17.920 --> 00:08:21.160
We didn't think that Neverland
was going to be the place

157
00:08:21.240 --> 00:08:23.680
where this whole thing unraveled.

158
00:08:24.200 --> 00:08:26.200
[ominous music playing]

159
00:08:33.320 --> 00:08:37.040
[Martin] When I got onto Neverland.
I couldn't believe what I was seeing.

160
00:08:37.120 --> 00:08:38.200
It was extraordinary.

161
00:08:38.280 --> 00:08:40.720
There was this Ferris wheel.
a massive fairground.

162
00:08:40.800 --> 00:08:42.920
And then I rode towards the zoo.

163
00:08:43.000 --> 00:08:47.080
and I can remember seeing elephants.
giraffes. and a bear.

164
00:08:48.520 --> 00:08:53.200
I made it clear
that I wanted to understand his life.

165
00:08:54.080 --> 00:08:57.600
I thought he had
a strange relationship with children.

166
00:08:57.680 --> 00:09:01.760
There had been allegations before.
There had been settlements.

167
00:09:04.120 --> 00:09:05.720
Do you come out here on your own?

168
00:09:05.800 --> 00:09:07.520
- Yeah.
- How often?

169
00:09:07.600 --> 00:09:09.640
- All the time.
- You just come out on your own?

170
00:09:09.720 --> 00:09:11.360
- Yes.
- What. and go on a ride?

171
00:09:11.440 --> 00:09:12.440
Yup.

172
00:09:12.520 --> 00:09:14.760
Usually the carousel. I'll play music.

173
00:09:14.840 --> 00:09:17.720
I love playing classical music
on the carousel.

174
00:09:17.800 --> 00:09:19.960
And what about the Ferris wheel?

175
00:09:20.040 --> 00:09:22.920
I like the Ferris wheel.
It makes you wish and dream andâ€¦

176
00:09:23.000 --> 00:09:24.640
- [Martin] Can we go on it?
- [Michael] Sure.

177
00:09:24.720 --> 00:09:25.800
[Martin] Let's go on it.

178
00:09:26.520 --> 00:09:28.600
When I met him.

179
00:09:28.680 --> 00:09:32.400
he was increasingly isolated as a figure.

180
00:09:32.480 --> 00:09:33.560
[pensive music playing]

181
00:09:33.640 --> 00:09:37.920
There was none of the kind
of lawyers and PR and publicists

182
00:09:38.000 --> 00:09:41.760
that normally surrounds
a major global superstar.

183
00:09:41.840 --> 00:09:43.320
He was in control.

184
00:09:43.400 --> 00:09:46.560
It was his idea
that we film in the dance studio.

185
00:09:48.760 --> 00:09:53.040
I knew I had to ask him certain questions
that were going to be quite difficult.

186
00:09:53.120 --> 00:09:54.960
But it was quite intimidating.

187
00:09:55.040 --> 00:09:57.080
When you're dealing with
someone like Michael Jackson.

188
00:09:57.160 --> 00:10:00.400
you don't tell him
what you're going to film.

189
00:10:00.480 --> 00:10:05.040
But if we behaved appropriately.
and if he liked us.

190
00:10:05.120 --> 00:10:06.920
then things would happen.

191
00:10:07.600 --> 00:10:09.040
Use your heel to slide back.

192
00:10:11.360 --> 00:10:13.880
- That is not easy. That is not easy.
- Really?

193
00:10:15.160 --> 00:10:17.400
- [laughing] That's not easy.
- That's very good. though.

194
00:10:17.480 --> 00:10:19.520
- That's the idea.
- You're a very kind man.

195
00:10:19.600 --> 00:10:20.640
[pensive music continues]

196
00:10:20.720 --> 00:10:22.240
I bought these.

197
00:10:22.320 --> 00:10:25.920
- These. Right?
- [Martin] You got enough space for it all?

198
00:10:26.000 --> 00:10:27.600
- [Michael] Yeah. I do.
- [Martin] You do?

199
00:10:27.680 --> 00:10:29.120
[Michael] Yeah. and these we bought.

200
00:10:29.200 --> 00:10:31.000
Okay. let's have a look at these ones.

201
00:10:31.080 --> 00:10:31.960
They're beautiful.

202
00:10:32.040 --> 00:10:34.840
[Martin] That's only 275.000 each.

203
00:10:36.400 --> 00:10:39.360
I was getting on well with him.

204
00:10:39.440 --> 00:10:42.320
The filming had gone really well.
He seemed to have enjoyed it.

205
00:10:43.040 --> 00:10:45.840
Yet I knew
that for this section of the film.

206
00:10:45.920 --> 00:10:50.400
I actually had to put all of that aside

207
00:10:50.480 --> 00:10:53.520
and behave as if
I was confronting him for the first time.

208
00:10:53.600 --> 00:10:55.600
[music turns ominous]

209
00:10:56.600 --> 00:11:00.400
I had to ask him about the allegations
of child sexual abuse.

210
00:11:00.480 --> 00:11:03.160
I was anxious
about what was going to happen

211
00:11:03.240 --> 00:11:06.520
when I put these
difficult questions to him.

212
00:11:07.800 --> 00:11:11.880
But as we moved towards
the end of the filming.

213
00:11:11.960 --> 00:11:14.400
