214
00:11:16.120 --> 00:11:19.120
So I said.
"Right. who do you want me to meet?"

215
00:11:19.200 --> 00:11:23.680
He said. "He's a little boy.
and we've healed him of cancer."

216
00:11:24.280 --> 00:11:28.200
Michael then gets up and goes out
and brings the child in front of us.

217
00:11:28.280 --> 00:11:30.280
{\an8}[unsettling music playing]

218
00:11:31.600 --> 00:11:34.520
{\an8}I think what was
going through his mind was.

219
00:11:34.600 --> 00:11:37.640
{\an8}"Here's an example
of a child that I've helped."

220
00:11:37.720 --> 00:11:41.160
"That's what I want you
to put in your film."

221
00:11:41.960 --> 00:11:46.640
And then Michael volunteers
during the conversation

222
00:11:46.720 --> 00:11:48.880
that they sleep in the bed together.

223
00:11:49.640 --> 00:11:51.400
{\an8}Why can't you share your bed?

224
00:11:52.080 --> 00:11:56.320
{\an8}The most loving thing to do
is to share your bed with someone.

225
00:11:56.400 --> 00:11:57.760
{\an8}- You know?
- [Martin] You think that?

226
00:11:57.840 --> 00:11:59.000
{\an8}Yeah.

227
00:11:59.800 --> 00:12:01.560
[unsettling music continues]

228
00:12:01.640 --> 00:12:03.840
[scoffs] And we're just utter--

229
00:12:03.920 --> 00:12:07.840
All of us. the production team.
are completely gobsmacked.

230
00:12:07.920 --> 00:12:11.720
{\an8}I mean. we can't believe
what's going on in front of us.

231
00:12:11.800 --> 00:12:13.560
{\an8}But haven't you got a spare room

232
00:12:13.640 --> 00:12:16.280
{\an8}or a spare house here
where he could have stayed?

233
00:12:16.360 --> 00:12:18.400
{\an8}Yeah. but no-- Yes. we have guest units.

234
00:12:18.480 --> 00:12:21.360
{\an8}But whenever kids come here.
they always want to stay with me.

235
00:12:21.440 --> 00:12:24.160
He'd actually made a disclosure on camera

236
00:12:24.240 --> 00:12:27.600
about something that had always
been queried around him.

237
00:12:27.680 --> 00:12:29.160
that people had always suspected

238
00:12:29.240 --> 00:12:31.920
there's something wrong
about the way he interacts.

239
00:12:32.000 --> 00:12:36.120
I realized that we had something
that was hugely significant.

240
00:12:36.200 --> 00:12:39.800
but I didn't realize the extent
of the bombshell until the broadcast.

241
00:12:40.400 --> 00:12:43.400
{\an8}[orchestral music swelling]

242
00:12:45.160 --> 00:12:46.960
Michael Jackson's home. Neverland.

243
00:12:47.040 --> 00:12:51.400
is a 3.000-acre ranch
three hours north of Los Angeles.

244
00:12:53.800 --> 00:12:58.280
<i>He thought about it. and then he said.</i>
<i>"Yes. come to Neverland."</i>

245
00:12:58.360 --> 00:13:01.760
What do you think
people would say if I said.

246
00:13:01.840 --> 00:13:04.960
"Well. I've invited some
of my daughter's friends round.

247
00:13:05.040 --> 00:13:07.280
or my son's friends.
to sleep in the bed with me tonight?"

248
00:13:07.360 --> 00:13:10.080
- [Michael] <i>That's fine!</i>
- [Martin] <i>What would their parents say?</i>

249
00:13:10.160 --> 00:13:12.760
[Michael] <i>If they're wacky.</i>
<i>they would say. "You can't."</i>

250
00:13:12.840 --> 00:13:16.000
But when you say "bed."
you're thinking sexual.

251
00:13:16.080 --> 00:13:18.440
They make that sexual. It's not sexual.

252
00:13:18.520 --> 00:13:19.920
- [Martin] Butâ€¦
- We're going to sleep.

253
00:13:20.000 --> 00:13:23.960
I tuck them in.
I put a little. like. music on.

254
00:13:24.040 --> 00:13:26.160
do a little story time. I read a book.

255
00:13:26.240 --> 00:13:29.400
It's very sweet.
Put the fireplace on. give them hot milk.

256
00:13:29.480 --> 00:13:31.000
You know. we have little cookies.

257
00:13:31.080 --> 00:13:33.120
- It's very charming. very sweet.
- Are you sure?

258
00:13:33.760 --> 00:13:35.800
[Randy] I'm watching Michael
on television.

259
00:13:35.880 --> 00:13:38.400
and there's a moment.
and if you knew him like I did.

260
00:13:38.480 --> 00:13:43.640
you can see him suddenly calculating
in his head that this is terrible.

261
00:13:43.720 --> 00:13:48.160
{\an8}He finally said. "Okay. if you love me.
let's sleep on the bed."

262
00:13:48.240 --> 00:13:50.240
{\an8}I was like. "Oh man."

263
00:13:50.320 --> 00:13:52.240
{\an8}[Randy] You can see it.

264
00:13:52.320 --> 00:13:55.400
{\an8}You can look at that moment
in the Martin Bashir documentary.

265
00:13:55.480 --> 00:13:59.360
and you can actually
pin the end of his life.

266
00:13:59.440 --> 00:14:01.040
you know. to that very moment.

267
00:14:01.120 --> 00:14:03.720
[dramatic music playing]

268
00:14:06.920 --> 00:14:09.120
Did you see that documentary
on Michael Jackson?

269
00:14:09.200 --> 00:14:11.080
He says he was devastated by it.

270
00:14:11.160 --> 00:14:13.120
Well. he talked about his plastic surgery

271
00:14:13.200 --> 00:14:16.480
and how he still invites
little children to sleep in his bed.

272
00:14:20.960 --> 00:14:22.600
{\an8}Of course. I tuned in.

273
00:14:22.680 --> 00:14:25.400
{\an8}My husband and I were watching. rapt.

274
00:14:26.240 --> 00:14:31.160
{\an8}And then I saw that boy
sitting on the sofa next to him

275
00:14:31.240 --> 00:14:33.360
{\an8}holding Jackson's hand.

276
00:14:33.440 --> 00:14:37.600
{\an8}putting his head on his shoulder.
looking up at him dreamily.

277
00:14:37.680 --> 00:14:40.600
{\an8}And I looked at my husband.
and I said. "Uh-oh."

278
00:14:41.280 --> 00:14:42.960
{\an8}I thought. "Here we go again."

279
00:14:43.040 --> 00:14:47.720
It drew me right back in to a story
that I had done ten years earlier.

280
00:14:47.800 --> 00:14:49.800
[unsettling music playing]

281
00:14:52.320 --> 00:14:54.400
The boy's name was Jordy Chandler.

282
00:14:55.520 --> 00:14:57.000
It never came to trial.

283
00:14:57.600 --> 00:15:00.640
Michael Jackson settled with the family

284
00:15:01.400 --> 00:15:03.840
for about $20 million.

285
00:15:04.880 --> 00:15:10.120
I suppose the problem for many people
is what happened in 1993.

286
00:15:10.200 --> 00:15:11.320
or what didn't happen.

287
00:15:11.400 --> 00:15:12.960
What didn't happen.

288
00:15:13.040 --> 00:15:16.160
"Nothing ever happened." It was a mantra.

289
00:15:16.240 --> 00:15:18.520
"Nothing ever happened."

290
00:15:19.120 --> 00:15:20.840
And I thought to myselfâ€¦

291
00:15:22.440 --> 00:15:23.560
"Maybe it did."

292
00:15:24.880 --> 00:15:28.280
[Martin on TV] <i>The reason that's been</i>
<i>given for why you didn't go to jail</i>

293
00:15:28.360 --> 00:15:32.560
<i>was because you reached</i>
<i>a financial settlement with the family.</i>

294
00:15:32.640 --> 00:15:33.640
<i>Yeah.</i>

295
00:15:33.720 --> 00:15:37.360
<i>I don't want to do a long.</i>
<i>drawn-out thing on TV like OJ.</i>

296
00:15:37.440 --> 00:15:39.240
<i>I want to go on with my life.</i>

297
00:15:39.320 --> 00:15:42.760
[Diane] Here it was. in my face again.
all those years later.

298
00:15:42.840 --> 00:15:45.280
and I couldn't ignore it.

299
00:15:45.360 --> 00:15:46.640
You can't ignore it.

300
00:15:46.720 --> 00:15:48.440
[unsettling music continues]

301
00:15:48.520 --> 00:15:53.800
[man] I just remember watching
the documentary with the Jackson family.

302
00:15:53.880 --> 00:15:56.080
{\an8}And they were shocked.

303
00:15:57.400 --> 00:15:59.320
And Michael. he called his mom.

304
00:15:59.400 --> 00:16:02.360
and her whole demeanor changed.

305
00:16:02.440 --> 00:16:06.240
Like. all she could say was.
"They set him up. They set him up."

306
00:16:06.840 --> 00:16:09.120
[man 1 on TV]
<i>Devastated and utterly betrayed.</i>

307
00:16:09.200 --> 00:16:10.720
<i>A gross distortion of the truth</i>

308
00:16:10.800 --> 00:16:14.960
<i>and a tawdry attempt to misrepresent</i>
<i>his life and his abilities as a father.</i>

309
00:16:15.040 --> 00:16:18.400
<i>That's the star's reaction</i>
<i>to </i>Living with Michael Jackson.

310
00:16:18.480 --> 00:16:21.200
[Randy] People thought something's
going on with Michael and this kid

311
00:16:21.280 --> 00:16:23.320
because of what we saw on TV.

312
00:16:23.400 --> 00:16:27.160
But Michael was determined
and ready to fight.

313
00:16:27.240 --> 00:16:29.760
Raymone Bain
is Michael Jackson's spokesperson.

314
00:16:29.840 --> 00:16:31.560
Ms. Bain. good morning to you.

315
00:16:31.640 --> 00:16:33.440
Good morning. How are you?

316
00:16:33.520 --> 00:16:36.680
{\an8}Well. I've been. uh. very blessed

317
00:16:37.480 --> 00:16:42.960
because I worked with Muhammad Ali.
Boyz II Men. Serena Williamsâ€¦

318
00:16:43.680 --> 00:16:48.280
And it was through Serena
recommending me to Michael Jackson

319
00:16:48.360 --> 00:16:50.800
that I began working for Michael Jackson.

320
00:16:50.880 --> 00:16:55.760
I thought that the Bashir documentary
was outrageous.

321
00:16:55.840 --> 00:16:58.240
It was a "I got you" kind of thing.

322
00:16:58.320 --> 00:17:04.400
After that. Michael was guilty
until found innocent.

323
00:17:04.480 --> 00:17:07.600
And I asked him point-blank.
looking dead in his face.

324
00:17:07.680 --> 00:17:08.800
"Did you do this?"

325
00:17:08.880 --> 00:17:11.480
And I was convinced when he told me no

326
00:17:11.560 --> 00:17:13.120
because had he told me yes.

327
00:17:13.200 --> 00:17:16.560
or had I thought that he was guilty
of molesting children.

328
00:17:16.640 --> 00:17:18.560
I wouldn't have represented him.

329
00:17:19.280 --> 00:17:22.680
One of the things
that I was concerned about.

330
00:17:22.760 --> 00:17:25.360
it was just uncontrollable.

331
00:17:25.440 --> 00:17:27.800
When you are bigger than life.

332
00:17:28.560 --> 00:17:29.880
which he was.

333
00:17:29.960 --> 00:17:32.000
nothing goes unreported.

334
00:17:32.080 --> 00:17:37.640
And there were some during that time
to make sure everything was reported.

335
00:17:39.000 --> 00:17:44.520
[Diane] I got on the line to all
my best sources within law enforcement

336
00:17:44.600 --> 00:17:48.120
to try to find out who this kid
in the Bashir documentary was.

337
00:17:48.200 --> 00:17:50.440
They said his name is Gavin.
That's all I know.

338
00:17:50.520 --> 00:17:52.720
[pensive music playing]

339
00:17:52.800 --> 00:17:54.800
[man] Everyone is saying.
"Who is the kid?"

340
00:17:54.880 --> 00:17:58.520
It's a bit like there's blood in the water
and the sharks are hungry.

341
00:17:58.600 --> 00:18:01.320
{\an8}And we were some of those sharks.
We were circling.

342
00:18:01.400 --> 00:18:03.640
{\an8}We were circling Neverland
to find that kid.

343
00:18:03.720 --> 00:18:06.640
You've got to remember how many people
are employed at Neverland.

344
00:18:06.720 --> 00:18:09.160
You've got people shoveling giraffe shit.

345
00:18:09.240 --> 00:18:11.040
You've got fairground workers.

346
00:18:11.120 --> 00:18:14.440
There's so many sources there.
There's so many employees.

347
00:18:14.520 --> 00:18:16.200
You know. we'reâ€¦ we're paying a few.

348
00:18:16.280 --> 00:18:18.840
[ominous music playing]

349
00:18:20.040 --> 00:18:22.480
It doesn't take long to get the name.

350
00:18:24.040 --> 00:18:26.840
The boy's surname was Arvizo.

351
00:18:26.920 --> 00:18:28.520
Gavin Arvizo.

352
00:18:28.600 --> 00:18:30.800
The difficulty. of course.
is you're dealing with a child.

353
00:18:30.880 --> 00:18:32.640
so we're going after the family.

354
00:18:32.720 --> 00:18:35.480
The dad. David Arvizo. we found him.

355
00:18:35.560 --> 00:18:38.120
The dad was ostracized from the family.

356
00:18:38.200 --> 00:18:40.560
So you've got a financially needy family

357
00:18:40.640 --> 00:18:43.280
whose head could be turned
by a large check.

358
00:18:44.120 --> 00:18:48.120
But in the case of the Arvizos.
they weren't selling their story.

359
00:18:48.200 --> 00:18:49.480
They never went for the money.

360
00:18:50.760 --> 00:18:53.840
There was a story to be had.
We just couldn't get it.

361
00:18:56.240 --> 00:18:58.240
[ominous music continues]

362
00:19:01.680 --> 00:19:04.240
[woman] A few years
prior to the documentary.

363
00:19:04.320 --> 00:19:07.600
I met the Arvizo family
at the Laugh Factory.

364
00:19:07.680 --> 00:19:12.400
{\an8}And Gavin was a really funny.

365
00:19:12.480 --> 00:19:14.040
{\an8}bright. sparkly kid.

366
00:19:14.120 --> 00:19:18.360
They were living in what you would call
a bachelor apartment. It was one room.

367
00:19:18.440 --> 00:19:21.080
They had mattresses on the floor.

368
00:19:21.160 --> 00:19:24.320
They had sheets
strung up for some privacy.

369
00:19:25.120 --> 00:19:27.200
Janet was a good mom.

370
00:19:27.280 --> 00:19:32.280
I found her to be childlike
in her enthusiasm for everything.

371
00:19:33.080 --> 00:19:37.640
And then one day. I get a phone call
from Janet. and she's screaming.

372
00:19:37.720 --> 00:19:39.520
"Gavin has cancer."

373
00:19:39.600 --> 00:19:42.000
[poignant music playing]

374
00:19:42.080 --> 00:19:45.280
As soon as I could.
I went down to the hospital.

375
00:19:45.360 --> 00:19:47.560
He was at Kaiser in Hollywood.

376
00:19:47.640 --> 00:19:51.480
They were going to try everything.
but the likelihood was that he would die.

377
00:19:53.880 --> 00:19:57.160
I would visit him frequently
at the hospital.

378
00:19:57.240 --> 00:19:58.840
He lost all his hair.

379
00:20:00.000 --> 00:20:04.080
Heâ€¦ He couldn't eat.
He was just rocking and moaning.

380
00:20:05.080 --> 00:20:07.480
One day. I walked into Gavin's room.

381
00:20:07.560 --> 00:20:10.800
and there was
a specially large gift basket.

382
00:20:10.880 --> 00:20:14.200
It was the size of half the room.

383
00:20:14.280 --> 00:20:17.080
I said. "Hey. Gav.
you know. who sent you that?"

384
00:20:17.160 --> 00:20:19.080
And he just said. "Michael."

385
00:20:19.760 --> 00:20:21.640
And I said. "Michael who?"

386
00:20:22.160 --> 00:20:23.400
"Michael Jackson."

387
00:20:24.560 --> 00:20:26.160
Okay. cool.

388
00:20:26.840 --> 00:20:28.280
I just sort of accepted it

389
00:20:28.360 --> 00:20:32.400
because we've all seen him
visiting all of these sick children

390
00:20:32.480 --> 00:20:34.120
and needy children.

391
00:20:34.200 --> 00:20:36.200
[women yell enthusiastically]

392
00:20:37.000 --> 00:20:39.720
Children will always
hold a special place in my heart.

393
00:20:39.800 --> 00:20:41.600
[children clamoring]

394
00:20:41.680 --> 00:20:46.000
[Louise] You'd just see a row of kids.
and Michael Jackson in the center.

395
00:20:46.840 --> 00:20:50.680
{\an8}[woman on TV] <i>Michael Jackson</i>
<i>was a modern-day Pied Piper to children.</i>

396
00:20:50.760 --> 00:20:55.320
{\an8}<i>He did tell me the children</i>
<i>coming to Neverland lifted his spirits.</i>

397
00:20:56.720 --> 00:20:58.280
{\an8}[Louise] A few months later.

398
00:20:58.360 --> 00:21:01.320
{\an8}Janet called me
and told me they had been to Neverland.

399
00:21:01.400 --> 00:21:04.800
{\an8}And she told me how wonderful Michael was.

400
00:21:04.880 --> 00:21:08.600
{\an8}And I thought that he was dying.
and why shouldn't he go enjoy Neverland?

401
00:21:09.920 --> 00:21:14.240
Well. way later. when I watched
the Martin Bashir documentary.

402
00:21:14.320 --> 00:21:15.320
my heart sank.

403
00:21:15.400 --> 00:21:18.440
I just immediately thought.
"The press is gonna hound these people."

404
00:21:18.520 --> 00:21:21.200
I did not want them in this whirlwind.

405
00:21:22.200 --> 00:21:25.120
I called Janet. I called Janet's mom.

406
00:21:25.200 --> 00:21:27.640
and every number I called
was disconnected.

407
00:21:28.480 --> 00:21:30.880
Their phones being disconnected
I found very alarming.

408
00:21:30.960 --> 00:21:32.120
[music fades]

409
00:21:32.200 --> 00:21:35.160
I didn't know their whereabouts.
I didn't know if they were safe.

410
00:21:36.760 --> 00:21:39.480
[ominous music playing]

411
00:21:39.560 --> 00:21:41.400
[man] I just had graduated college.

412
00:21:41.480 --> 00:21:45.040
{\an8}I was very excited to work
in the entertainment industry

413
00:21:45.120 --> 00:21:46.880
{\an8}and for Michael Jackson.

414
00:21:47.600 --> 00:21:49.720
When I arrived in Los Angeles.

415
00:21:49.800 --> 00:21:52.440
I walked into a very busy house.

416
00:21:52.520 --> 00:21:55.960
comparable to. like.
walking into. like. a busy newsroom.

417
00:21:56.840 --> 00:21:59.800
People running around.
phones ringing off the hook.

418
00:21:59.880 --> 00:22:04.320
The media agencies were calling nonstop.

419
00:22:04.400 --> 00:22:09.360
So I walk into this damage control.
and then they said.

420
00:22:09.440 --> 00:22:11.520
"You're gonna take care
of the Arvizo family."

421
00:22:11.600 --> 00:22:16.240
The media wanted answers
after the fallout of the Bashir special.

422
00:22:16.320 --> 00:22:20.840
Michael graciously opened up his arms
and allowed the Arvizos back to the ranch.

423
00:22:20.920 --> 00:22:24.400
So they were
weathering the storm at Neverland.

424
00:22:24.480 --> 00:22:28.240
[music crescendos. fades]

425
00:22:28.840 --> 00:22:31.040
These photos are from the ranch.

426
00:22:31.120 --> 00:22:34.080
I've kept them for the last 20 years.

427
00:22:34.160 --> 00:22:37.080
This is Gavin's mother. Janet Arvizo.

428
00:22:37.160 --> 00:22:43.680
{\an8}She writes. "Dearest loving Michael.
we appreciate you being our family."

429
00:22:43.760 --> 00:22:47.960
{\an8}"What God brings together.
no man can undo."

430
00:22:48.040 --> 00:22:49.320
{\an8}"We love you."

431
00:22:49.400 --> 00:22:51.400
[unsettling music playing]

432
00:22:53.040 --> 00:22:57.080
This is Star Arvizo. Gavin's brother.

433
00:22:58.320 --> 00:23:04.080
{\an8}"I love you. my daddy Michael.
Your son. Blowhole."

434
00:23:05.440 --> 00:23:08.880
These are the nicknames that Michael
would give theseâ€¦ these young boys.

435
00:23:10.960 --> 00:23:13.600
There was individuals in the media

436
00:23:13.680 --> 00:23:16.640
questioning Michael's relationship
with children.

437
00:23:17.600 --> 00:23:22.920
So the Jackson camp felt a need to hire
a criminal defense attorney. Mark Geragos.

438
00:23:23.480 --> 00:23:26.040
to look over the legal aspects of this.

439
00:23:27.200 --> 00:23:29.280
[man] I had received a call

440
00:23:29.360 --> 00:23:35.680
from a gentleman
who was representing Michael.

441
00:23:36.280 --> 00:23:39.880
And he asked if I would
meet Michael at Neverland.

442
00:23:40.720 --> 00:23:43.200
{\an8}The DNA of being a criminal defense lawyer

443
00:23:43.280 --> 00:23:46.520
{\an8}is you're always thinking about
the worst that can happen.

444
00:23:47.120 --> 00:23:52.680
I realized that this is not just
a reputation management issue.

445
00:23:52.760 --> 00:23:56.200
This is potentially criminal exposure.

446
00:23:56.280 --> 00:23:58.720
- And that is a problem.
- [ominous music playing]

447
00:23:59.760 --> 00:24:03.440
I saw that this was red meat

448
00:24:03.520 --> 00:24:08.200
for a prosecutor who was determined
to take down Michael.

449
00:24:08.880 --> 00:24:12.120
The Jackson associates
decided to make a video.

450
00:24:13.120 --> 00:24:16.840
Janet Arvizo and family was to be filmed.

451
00:24:17.480 --> 00:24:21.800
providing truthful statements regarding
Michael Jackson and their relationship.

452
00:24:21.880 --> 00:24:25.760
and more importantly.
Gavin's relationship with Michael Jackson.

453
00:24:26.920 --> 00:24:29.520
{\an8}Wait. you know how these Bashirâ€¦

454
00:24:29.600 --> 00:24:34.280
{\an8}Hey. you know how Bashir
zoomed in on him holding hands?

455
00:24:34.360 --> 00:24:36.480
{\an8}- Do that. the same thing.
- 'Cause you know howâ€¦

456
00:24:36.560 --> 00:24:39.680
{\an8}Because that's what a mother
or a father does with a son.

457
00:24:39.760 --> 00:24:43.760
{\an8}And I feel that Janet. in front of me.
while I was watching.

458
00:24:43.840 --> 00:24:46.560
gave her side of the truth

459
00:24:46.640 --> 00:24:48.800
about her relationship
with Michael Jackson

460
00:24:48.880 --> 00:24:51.200
that was not scripted.

461
00:24:51.280 --> 00:24:52.640
{\an8}When I would tell him.

462
00:24:52.720 --> 00:24:54.840
{\an8}"The doctors are saying
there's no chance."

463
00:24:54.920 --> 00:24:57.480
{\an8}Michael said. "I will not have that."

464
00:24:57.560 --> 00:25:01.280
{\an8}"You bring him to me.
and we will coat him with love."

465
00:25:01.360 --> 00:25:04.640
{\an8}We may be broken. Michael fixed us.

466
00:25:04.720 --> 00:25:07.880
{\an8}[Vincent] I physically watched
and believed her responses to be true.

467
00:25:07.960 --> 00:25:11.960
and nothing ever occurred
untoward to them by Michael Jackson.

468
00:25:12.560 --> 00:25:17.560
{\an8}When I first met Michael. all I thought
