00:37:01.800 --> 00:37:05.200
And it's a bit embarrassing
that we don't know where he is right now.

707
00:37:05.280 --> 00:37:06.480
[ominous music continues]

708
00:37:06.560 --> 00:37:09.560
[Brian] Those of us
who know Michael. we thinkâ€¦

709
00:37:09.640 --> 00:37:10.840
I think the world of him.

710
00:37:10.920 --> 00:37:13.960
and I just cannot fathom
that this would be true.

711
00:37:14.040 --> 00:37:17.480
At the time.
Michael wasn't talking to nobody.

712
00:37:17.560 --> 00:37:20.040
He was hoping
that the furor would go away.

713
00:37:20.120 --> 00:37:22.640
Mrs. Jackson had a theory about life.

714
00:37:22.720 --> 00:37:27.240
If you ducked and covered enough.
the storm would pass you by.

715
00:37:27.320 --> 00:37:30.280
And Michael practiced that very carefully.

716
00:37:31.880 --> 00:37:35.720
[Diane] I find out from a source.
he's holed up in this villa.

717
00:37:35.800 --> 00:37:40.960
and he only opens the door wearing
a colorful dashiki muumuu garment.

718
00:37:41.040 --> 00:37:44.480
only enough to get the food brought in.
and then he slams the door.

719
00:37:44.560 --> 00:37:46.880
And he's having wild parties.

720
00:37:47.480 --> 00:37:51.400
There were cigarette burns
in the leather couches and chairs.

721
00:37:51.480 --> 00:37:53.720
There were food containers everywhere.

722
00:37:53.800 --> 00:37:57.120
There were empty liquor bottles
on every table.

723
00:37:57.200 --> 00:38:00.680
And this is where Michael Jackson
had been for several days.

724
00:38:00.760 --> 00:38:05.960
entertaining young teenage boys
who all spoke German.

725
00:38:06.800 --> 00:38:10.720
And he said. after the raid.
Michael Jackson was informed.

726
00:38:10.800 --> 00:38:13.680
"Oh my God.
the cops are at Neverland again."

727
00:38:13.760 --> 00:38:16.080
And he left just like that.

728
00:38:16.160 --> 00:38:18.160
[ominous music continues]

729
00:38:20.560 --> 00:38:23.080
[Diane] Michael Jackson remains
a wanted man this morning.

730
00:38:23.160 --> 00:38:26.640
and everyone's waiting
to see when he'll turn himself in.

731
00:38:27.400 --> 00:38:30.680
Jackson's spokesman says
the singer will return to Santa Barbara

732
00:38:30.760 --> 00:38:34.040
to confront and prove
that the charges are unfounded.

733
00:38:34.120 --> 00:38:36.600
We have to go.
My producer's telling me we have to go.

734
00:38:36.680 --> 00:38:39.200
The next thing I hear.
Michael Jackson negotiates

735
00:38:39.280 --> 00:38:41.440
with the district attorney's office

736
00:38:41.520 --> 00:38:43.520
as to the "surrender."

737
00:38:43.600 --> 00:38:45.600
[tense music playing]

738
00:38:48.880 --> 00:38:50.880
[man] We were hearing that this aircraft

739
00:38:50.960 --> 00:38:53.800
may be connected
with Michael Jackson's arrival.

740
00:38:53.880 --> 00:38:56.640
He is rolling out right now
on runway seven.

741
00:39:01.560 --> 00:39:03.840
{\an8}[Diane] He flew in in a private jet.

742
00:39:03.920 --> 00:39:06.240
{\an8}into a hangar in Santa Barbara.

743
00:39:06.800 --> 00:39:08.600
{\an8}and my sources were telling me

744
00:39:09.560 --> 00:39:13.040
{\an8}he voluntarily flew there to surrender.

745
00:39:15.440 --> 00:39:18.480
They put the handcuffs on him
and put him in a car.

746
00:39:18.560 --> 00:39:22.960
That car was also outfitted with audio.

747
00:39:23.040 --> 00:39:23.880
[man 1] <i>Okay.</i>

748
00:39:23.960 --> 00:39:25.720
[Michael] <i>Can we put some air on. please?</i>

749
00:39:25.800 --> 00:39:26.720
[man 1] <i>Okay.</i>

750
00:39:26.800 --> 00:39:28.320
[man 2] <i>That okay for you. Mr. Jackson?</i>

751
00:39:28.400 --> 00:39:30.960
[Michael] <i>It's wonderful. Thank you.</i>
<i>Thank you very much.</i>

752
00:39:32.000 --> 00:39:36.640
[Diane] They did not want
any false reports of police brutality.

753
00:39:36.720 --> 00:39:39.720
- [protesters yelling indistinctly]
- [tense music continues]

754
00:39:41.680 --> 00:39:43.120
[man 1] <i>Coming in the back.</i>

755
00:39:43.200 --> 00:39:44.240
[man 2] <i>The back.</i>

756
00:39:47.000 --> 00:39:48.160
[man 1] <i>He's coming in.</i>

757
00:39:49.840 --> 00:39:53.600
[man 3] It's the car starting to pull
into the sally port area.

758
00:39:55.920 --> 00:39:57.080
[speaking indistinctly]

759
00:39:57.160 --> 00:39:59.000
[Michael] <i>They hurt.</i>
<i>They're tight. aren't they?</i>

760
00:39:59.080 --> 00:40:01.320
[man 2] <i>Just. if you want</i>
<i>to scoot forward a little bit.</i>

761
00:40:01.400 --> 00:40:03.040
<i>There you go.</i>

762
00:40:03.120 --> 00:40:05.840
[man 3] All right.
somebody's coming out of the vehicle now.

763
00:40:05.920 --> 00:40:08.520
[Diane] There he is. It's Michael Jackson.

764
00:40:09.360 --> 00:40:10.320
He's in handcuffs.

765
00:40:10.400 --> 00:40:13.120
- [man 3] I believe he's in handcuffs.
- [Diane] Mike. he's in handcuffs.

766
00:40:13.200 --> 00:40:14.240
[man 3] Yes.

767
00:40:14.320 --> 00:40:17.440
[man 4] So after that 24-hour mystery
about his whereabouts.

768
00:40:17.520 --> 00:40:21.640
Michael Jackson has now surrendered
into police custody behind me.

769
00:40:21.720 --> 00:40:25.200
A crushing humiliation
for one of the world's great entertainers.

770
00:40:25.280 --> 00:40:29.680
right now being read those charges
of child molestation.

771
00:40:29.760 --> 00:40:32.720
Minutes are ticking by.
I'm still live on the air.

772
00:40:32.800 --> 00:40:36.880
I'm thinking. "Is he going to be booked.
fingerprinted. mugshot?"

773
00:40:36.960 --> 00:40:38.760
"What happens next?"

774
00:40:39.360 --> 00:40:42.520
And then it popped up
in my monitor. [gasps]

775
00:40:43.200 --> 00:40:44.600
And I was stunned.

776
00:40:45.440 --> 00:40:48.400
I'm live on the air.
so I have to be careful what I say.

777
00:40:48.480 --> 00:40:52.120
I thought. number one. he looks so pale.

778
00:40:52.200 --> 00:40:56.640
It looked ghoulish.
It looked like a deer in the headlights.

779
00:40:56.720 --> 00:40:58.400
I almost felt sorry for him.

780
00:40:59.200 --> 00:41:02.280
When I saw him with his hands cuffed.

781
00:41:02.360 --> 00:41:03.840
and then that mugshot.

782
00:41:03.920 --> 00:41:07.840
I realized this is not
just at the allegation stage anymore.

783
00:41:07.920 --> 00:41:12.200
Michael Jackson is now
in the American criminal justice system.

784
00:41:12.280 --> 00:41:13.240
He's in the system.

785
00:41:14.000 --> 00:41:16.480
And the system
was not going to let him go.

786
00:41:16.560 --> 00:41:20.720
and my sources were telling me
there was going to be a criminal trial.

787
00:41:20.800 --> 00:41:22.160
[ominous music playing]

788
00:41:22.240 --> 00:41:25.320
[man] Seven counts of lewd
and lascivious acts against a child

789
00:41:25.400 --> 00:41:29.400
with the intent of arousing.
appealing to. and gratifying the lust.

790
00:41:29.480 --> 00:41:32.480
passions. and sexual desires
of Jackson and the child.

791
00:41:32.560 --> 00:41:35.600
and two counts of administering
an intoxicating agent.

792
00:41:35.680 --> 00:41:37.040
reportedly alcohol.

793
00:41:37.120 --> 00:41:39.560
with the intent
of committing child molestation.

794
00:41:40.760 --> 00:41:45.480
[Mark] He's come back specifically
to confront these charges head-on.

795
00:41:45.560 --> 00:41:51.000
He is greatly outraged
by the bringing of these charges.

796
00:41:51.080 --> 00:41:53.920
Uh. he considers this to be a big lie.

797
00:41:54.000 --> 00:41:56.040
He was enormously stressed.

798
00:41:56.120 --> 00:42:02.600
{\an8}All of a sudden. there is a reality
to what has been theoretical.

799
00:42:02.680 --> 00:42:04.600
[ominous music continues]

800
00:42:04.680 --> 00:42:07.160
I watched him just disintegrate.

801
00:42:07.240 --> 00:42:08.880
Literally disintegrate.

802
00:42:10.960 --> 00:42:16.800
The ingestion of substances
was just astronomical.

803
00:42:17.760 --> 00:42:21.480
There was a time when I actually saw him
in the fetal position on the floor.

804
00:42:21.560 --> 00:42:23.840
and I thought. "What do we do?"

805
00:42:23.920 --> 00:42:28.560
I mean. you don't want his death
to be on your hands

806
00:42:28.640 --> 00:42:30.120
because you took some inaction.

807
00:42:33.280 --> 00:42:38.880
It was a horrific time for him
and for those around him.

808
00:42:38.960 --> 00:42:41.800
and we had genuine concerns as to whether

809
00:42:41.880 --> 00:42:45.600
he could even withstand a trial
physically. mentally.

810
00:42:45.680 --> 00:42:48.280
[ominous music continues]

811
00:42:48.360 --> 00:42:54.000
{\an8}Michael is hearing all of these heinous
accusations on a day-to-day basis.

812
00:42:54.080 --> 00:43:00.600
{\an8}and he's wanting people to step up and say
that's not true. and to defend him more.

813
00:43:00.680 --> 00:43:02.320
{\an8}[Joe] We know our son.

814
00:43:02.400 --> 00:43:06.640
{\an8}We know that he's not a pedophile
like some of these newscasters are saying.

815
00:43:06.720 --> 00:43:08.360
{\an8}This is ridiculous.

816
00:43:08.440 --> 00:43:12.360
{\an8}We have a lot of wicked people out there.
and they know what they're doing.

817
00:43:13.120 --> 00:43:16.920
[Raymone] Michael is saying.
"What is this obsession with me?"

818
00:43:17.000 --> 00:43:19.440
"Why am I a target?"

819
00:43:19.520 --> 00:43:25.320
It seemed to me that there was
a deliberate attempt to try to get him.

820
00:43:25.400 --> 00:43:27.560
{\an8}It is racism. It is.

821
00:43:27.640 --> 00:43:30.160
{\an8}Katherine's not going to say it.
but I will say it.

822
00:43:30.240 --> 00:43:31.760
{\an8}It is racism.

823
00:43:32.440 --> 00:43:34.800
[Stacy] When the charges
were announced against Michael.

824
00:43:34.880 --> 00:43:37.200
of course. the family.
they were heartsick.

825
00:43:37.280 --> 00:43:41.840
{\an8}But for Michael's siblings. it was never
about guilt or innocence for them.

826
00:43:41.920 --> 00:43:43.360
{\an8}It was about legacy.

827
00:43:43.960 --> 00:43:47.680
"They can't do this to us.
They want to destroy what we built."

828
00:43:47.760 --> 00:43:50.440
It's what I kept hearing
over and over again.

829
00:43:50.520 --> 00:43:53.920
We are the Jacksons.
as Randy Jackson would say. you know.

830
00:43:54.000 --> 00:43:56.080
"We're royalty. We're the Black Kennedys."

831
00:43:56.160 --> 00:43:57.680
[tense music playing]

832
00:43:57.760 --> 00:44:00.800
My mother. my father.
my sisters. my brothers

833
00:44:00.880 --> 00:44:05.160
are overwhelmed at the outpouring
of the support from the fans.

834
00:44:05.240 --> 00:44:08.200
both here in the United States
and all around the world.

835
00:44:08.280 --> 00:44:10.760
It was all about the brand.

836
00:44:10.840 --> 00:44:12.440
Michael Jackson. the brand.

837
00:44:12.520 --> 00:44:16.720
The Jacksons. the brand.
We've got to protect the brand.

838
00:44:17.440 --> 00:44:20.240
Thank you very much.
That's all I've got to say.

839
00:44:20.320 --> 00:44:23.280
[Stacy] I remember Jermaine calling me up
and says. "Guess what?"

840
00:44:23.360 --> 00:44:27.920
"You know. Michael says. when the trial
is over. we're going to go on tour again."

841
00:44:28.000 --> 00:44:31.320
And I got to realize that
that's what this was really about for--

842
00:44:31.400 --> 00:44:32.720
At least for Jermaine.

843
00:44:34.160 --> 00:44:37.200
We've got to support him
because he's got to come through this.

844
00:44:37.280 --> 00:44:40.880
he's got to beat these charges so they can
make more music and go out on tour.

845
00:44:41.480 --> 00:44:44.400
He's innocent.
And he knows that. We know that.

846
00:44:44.480 --> 00:44:46.880
And the public knows that too.

847
00:44:46.960 --> 00:44:48.280
He's innocent.

848
00:44:48.360 --> 00:44:50.720
{\an8}Our response is. here we go again.

849
00:44:50.800 --> 00:44:53.640
{\an8}Michael has 24-hour-a-day
supervision with him

850
00:44:53.720 --> 00:44:57.600
{\an8}for the specific purpose of protecting him
against these kinds of claims.

851
00:44:57.680 --> 00:45:00.520
{\an8}Did he want to have children around him?

852
00:45:00.600 --> 00:45:03.960
{\an8}Yes. he did. No question about it.

853
00:45:04.640 --> 00:45:07.680
But to groom children for molestation?

854
00:45:07.760 --> 00:45:10.480
What. he was the wicked witch
in <i>Hansel and Gretel?</i>

855
00:45:10.560 --> 00:45:11.800
How nonsensical.

856
00:45:12.680 --> 00:45:16.360
Michael Jackson was the biggest superstar

857
00:45:16.440 --> 00:45:19.240
in the history
of the country and the world.

858
00:45:19.320 --> 00:45:23.040
Adults would get into Michael's presence.
and they were all atwitter.

859
00:45:23.120 --> 00:45:26.000
and it was impossible for him to function.

860
00:45:26.080 --> 00:45:28.560
But with children. they didn't care.

861
00:45:29.080 --> 00:45:31.200
He was just one of the guys.

862
00:45:31.280 --> 00:45:34.080
And that's why he liked
being with children.

863
00:45:34.160 --> 00:45:37.160
- [crowd clamoring]
- [unsettling music playing]

864
00:45:38.120 --> 00:45:43.280
I remember on the day of the arraignment.
I'd never seen anything like it.

865
00:45:45.000 --> 00:45:47.480
Michael Jackson presents himself in court.

866
00:45:47.560 --> 00:45:50.720
and the formal charges
are read against him.

867
00:45:51.320 --> 00:45:55.400
I knew we were watching
the potential demise of a superstar.

868
00:45:55.480 --> 00:45:58.240
- [music turns tense]
- [crowd clamoring]

869
00:45:58.320 --> 00:46:00.080
- [woman] Michael.
- [man] Michael.

870
00:46:00.160 --> 00:46:03.160
He knows there are two
parallel battles underway.

871
00:46:03.240 --> 00:46:06.760
There is the legal battle underway
inside that courtroom.

872
00:46:06.840 --> 00:46:09.520
and then there is
the public relations skirmish

873
00:46:09.600 --> 00:46:11.440
that is also underway.

874
00:46:11.520 --> 00:46:12.720
[girls chanting] Michael!

875
00:46:12.800 --> 00:46:15.800
[Stacy] Michael had
an entire army with him.

876
00:46:15.880 --> 00:46:17.200
The huge crowd there.

877
00:46:17.280 --> 00:46:21.440
News stations take this garbage
and then report it as fact?

878
00:46:21.520 --> 00:46:23.640
- You should be ashamed of yourselves!
- [man] Ashamed.

879
00:46:23.720 --> 00:46:24.720
[women whoop]

880
00:46:24.800 --> 00:46:26.040
[girls chanting] Michael!

881
00:46:26.120 --> 00:46:30.120
I believe he's 100% innocent. and I don't
think he would do something like this.

882
00:46:30.200 --> 00:46:31.920
He doesn't have the heart to do it.

883
00:46:32.000 --> 00:46:35.000
We believe in his innocence.
and we're supporting him all the way.

884
00:46:35.080 --> 00:46:36.600
and we're thinking about him.

885
00:46:36.680 --> 00:46:38.600
and we're going to be here for him.

886
00:46:38.680 --> 00:46:40.320
- What do we want?
- [crowd] Justice!

887
00:46:40.400 --> 00:46:42.480
{\an8}- When do we want it? Now!
- [crowd] Now!

888
00:46:42.560 --> 00:46:44.280
[Stacy] I'll never forget Bob Jones.

889
00:46:44.360 --> 00:46:48.600
Michael's longtime manager.
and I were standing next to Michael.

890
00:46:48.680 --> 00:46:51.720
And Bob had his back to him.

891
00:46:51.800 --> 00:46:53.160
And he says.

892
00:46:53.240 --> 00:46:57.200
"I know he's gonna do something crazy.
I just know he's going to."

893
00:46:57.280 --> 00:46:58.600
[crowd screaming]

894
00:46:58.680 --> 00:47:02.240
[woman] Oh my goodness. look at this.
He's jumping on top of the car.

895
00:47:02.320 --> 00:47:06.160
- [man] Oh yeah. we see him.
- [woman] Truly performing for his fans.

896
00:47:07.280 --> 00:47:10.400
I remember looking up. kind of gobsmacked.

897
00:47:10.480 --> 00:47:12.680
and I thought he was
gonna start moonwalking.

898
00:47:12.760 --> 00:47:15.040
[crowd screaming]

899
00:47:15.120 --> 00:47:17.640
[Mark] I was immensely impressed

900
00:47:17.720 --> 00:47:22.520
with the physicality
of hopping onto the top of an SUV

901
00:47:22.600 --> 00:47:24.600
in the state or condition he was in.

902
00:47:25.240 --> 00:47:28.680
He's one of the greatest performers
of the century.

903
00:47:28.760 --> 00:47:29.840
He can turn it on.

904
00:47:31.200 --> 00:47:32.360
[Brian] He said.

905
00:47:32.440 --> 00:47:36.080
"Brian. how do guilty people leave court?"

906
00:47:36.160 --> 00:47:38.640
I said. "They kind of are embarrassed
and they hide."

907
00:47:38.720 --> 00:47:43.080
He says. "Yeah. they put their jacket
over their head. and they hide."

908
00:47:44.120 --> 00:47:47.560
"How do innocent people
leave the courthouse?"

909
00:47:48.840 --> 00:47:51.120
"They let the whole world see them."

910
00:47:51.800 --> 00:47:55.120
"They stand tall. and they stand proud."

911
00:47:55.200 --> 00:47:58.200
- [ominous music playing]
- [crowd screaming]

912
00:47:59.560 --> 00:48:03.560
In his own inimical way.

913
00:48:03.640 --> 00:48:07.680
Michael Jackson knew
how to tell the world he was innocent.

914
00:48:12.040 --> 00:48:14.360
[unsettling music playing]

915
00:48:14.440 --> 00:48:17.640
[Diane] I would not be surprised
if somewhere down the road.

916
00:48:17.720 --> 00:48:20.560
some of the people
surrounding Michael Jackson

917
00:48:20.640 --> 00:48:23.680
{\an8}might have at least the threat
of charges against them.

918
00:48:23.760 --> 00:48:26.640
{\an8}aiding. abetting. allowing children in.

919
00:48:26.720 --> 00:48:29.840
knowing full well
what the heck might happen.

920
00:48:30.440 --> 00:48:32.520
[on recording] <i>Hey. Vincent.</i>
<i>Sergeant Robel again.</i>

921
00:48:32.600 --> 00:48:33.720
<i>I want to hear from you.</i>

922
00:48:33.800 --> 00:48:36.120
<i>whether you want</i>
<i>to speak to me with your attorney.</i>

923
00:48:36.200 --> 00:48:40.400
<i>Giving you the opportunity. bud.</i>
<i>because the ship is sinking pretty fast.</i>

924
00:48:40.480 --> 00:48:42.520
<i>So. please. Vince. give me a buzz.</i>

925
00:48:43.560 --> 00:48:47.400
[Ron] You know. we knew that Vinny was
one of the people who was at Neverland

926
00:48:47.480 --> 00:48:50.240
{\an8}and had an association with the kids
when they were there.

927
00:48:50.320 --> 00:48:54.560
{\an8}So we were interested in talking to Vinny
to see if he could help us in any way

928
00:48:54.640 --> 00:48:57.360
{\an8}in terms of what was going on
with the kids.

929
00:48:57.440 --> 00:48:58.520
{\an8}I defended him.

930
00:48:59.800 --> 00:49:01.480
{\an8}And I believed in his innocence.

931
00:49:01.560 --> 00:49:04.520
{\an8}One of the reasons
was because of my friend Frank.

932
00:49:05.160 --> 00:49:07.240
Michael was like a father to Frank.

933
00:49:08.360 --> 00:49:11.640
Frank was a young child
when he met Michael.

934
00:49:11.720 --> 00:49:15.400
